WEBVTT

00:01.084 --> 00:02.752
NARRATOR:
Previously on Chesapeake Shores:

00:02.836 --> 00:05.005
-Been a pleasure working with you.
-You're leaving?

00:05.088 --> 00:07.132
-Does Mick know?
-It was his idea.

00:07.215 --> 00:09.801
HANNAH: If I was dating someone
with that much passion and charisma,

00:09.884 --> 00:11.928
-I'd be writing about my love life too.
-Yeah.

00:12.011 --> 00:15.348
BREE: Martin and I had passion.
Simon and I have conversations.

00:15.432 --> 00:17.600
Maybe you can talk your way into a kiss.

00:18.101 --> 00:19.144
Perfect.

00:19.227 --> 00:22.397
Kevin and I are still trying to figure out
what we wanna do for our wedding.

00:22.480 --> 00:24.065
It wouldn't hurt to start planning.

00:24.149 --> 00:26.609
ABBY:
I am about to blow the whistle on the Porter Fund.

00:26.693 --> 00:28.862
Abby, you're officially suspended without pay,

00:28.945 --> 00:30.947
pending a formal investigation.

00:31.990 --> 00:32.824
[♪♪♪]

00:32.907 --> 00:33.742
Thanks.

00:35.076 --> 00:37.287
So is it just me, or is this weird?

00:37.370 --> 00:38.747
That we're now engaged?

00:38.830 --> 00:40.707
We decided we're spending our lives together,

00:40.790 --> 00:43.877
but we haven't been able
to spend just one day alone.

00:43.960 --> 00:46.337
When you called, it was supposed
to be you and me, right?

00:46.421 --> 00:47.547
That's what I thought too.

00:47.630 --> 00:50.133
I agree, location is important.

00:50.216 --> 00:53.011
But you have to start with theme.
Theme dictates venue.

00:53.094 --> 00:56.139
Ooh, whimsical. Romantic. No, vintage.

00:56.222 --> 00:58.016
Mmm. Desert island.

00:58.099 --> 01:00.435
-Like the beach?
-No, like Gilligan and the Skipper.

01:00.518 --> 01:04.480
Is it just me, or do they maybe not want us to help?

01:04.563 --> 01:07.692
-They definitely don't want us to help.
BREE: Fine, we'll lay off.

01:07.776 --> 01:10.111
But Kevin's wedding signifies
an important family shift.

01:10.195 --> 01:14.657
It's a chance for all of us
to look forward and begin anew.

01:14.741 --> 01:16.618
And weddings are super fun.

01:16.701 --> 01:19.579
Seriously, you guys are way overthinking this.
It's like a year away.

01:19.662 --> 01:22.165
Connor, weddings are about being happy

01:22.248 --> 01:25.835
and joyful and positive
and hopeful about the future.

01:25.919 --> 01:27.253
-Do you want happy-joyful?
-Mm-hm.

01:27.337 --> 01:30.632
Well, then I'm happily doing research
for my uncle. Again.

01:30.715 --> 01:34.719
And I'm ecstatic we found the perfect inn
that someone else wants to buy.

01:34.803 --> 01:36.888
And I am overjoyed...

01:38.097 --> 01:39.808
about everything.

01:41.017 --> 01:43.228
Ice cream used to make everything better.

01:43.311 --> 01:45.188
Yeah, it's lost its magical power.

01:46.064 --> 01:49.192
So back to planning the wedding?

01:52.362 --> 01:54.114
[♪♪♪]

01:56.074 --> 01:58.535
Must be nice having control of your club back.

01:58.618 --> 02:01.996
Yeah, it is. It's one of the few things
that still feels like home.

02:02.080 --> 02:03.540
I get it.

02:03.623 --> 02:06.793
It's definitely feeling more like a place
where you'd wanna hear music.

02:06.876 --> 02:08.752
That's why I built the Bridge.

02:08.836 --> 02:11.339
I always dreamed of having my own venue.

02:11.422 --> 02:15.385
A place where up-and-coming artists
could develop their sound.

02:15.468 --> 02:18.555
-Is that how you found yours?
-Me? No, no.

02:18.638 --> 02:21.224
I always loved music because of my mom.

02:21.307 --> 02:24.936
But I didn't find my sound
until I got out on the road.

02:25.019 --> 02:27.063
And now you're back.

02:27.147 --> 02:29.440
That was always the plan.

02:29.524 --> 02:33.236
Give something back
to the industry that's given me so much.

02:33.319 --> 02:35.071
It's time for the next chapter in my life.

02:37.407 --> 02:40.743
But enough about me.
I don't know anything about you,

02:40.827 --> 02:43.288
except you're always late
coming back from breaks,

02:43.371 --> 02:45.665
and I'm pretty sure
you're not on the run from the law.

02:45.748 --> 02:48.001
-Pretty sure?
-I'd say fifty-fifty.

02:48.960 --> 02:53.298
Trust me, you don't wanna hear about me.
My life is pretty boring.

02:53.381 --> 02:54.215
Is that right?

02:55.592 --> 03:01.598
♪ Never been the kind
To wear a one-size-fits-all dream ♪♪

03:01.681 --> 03:03.558
How do you know my song?

03:03.641 --> 03:06.269
-You heard it once.
-When I like something, I don't forget it.

03:07.770 --> 03:10.565
So, what's it about?

03:11.649 --> 03:16.738
I wrote it about my boyfriend. Well, ex-boyfriend.

03:16.821 --> 03:19.449
He was gonna be some big rock star.

03:19.532 --> 03:22.994
And I was supposed
to follow him around the country,

03:23.077 --> 03:24.203
be at his beck and call.

03:24.287 --> 03:25.455
And what happened?

03:26.122 --> 03:28.416
I decided I deserved better
and ditched him in Atlanta.

03:30.460 --> 03:34.255
He never really treated me that well.
It was all about him.

03:34.339 --> 03:38.092
-Well, at least you got a song out of it.
-Half a song.

03:38.176 --> 03:43.848
-I guess I'm still trying to figure it all out.
-Well, you came to the right place.

03:43.932 --> 03:45.934
[PLAYING GUITAR]

03:51.981 --> 03:54.776
♪ Plane ticket already paid ♪

03:54.859 --> 03:57.570
♪ I'm gone
But it don't mean nothing ♪

03:57.654 --> 04:01.699
♪ I'm close even though I'm far away ♪

04:03.493 --> 04:06.204
♪ That's how I remember you ♪

04:06.287 --> 04:08.998
♪ Stuck here on the red-eye special ♪

04:09.082 --> 04:13.002
♪ I can't wait to see you again ♪

04:14.837 --> 04:18.925
♪ So don't think of me
Not being around ♪

04:20.885 --> 04:26.724
♪ Just listen for the sweet, sweet sound
Of the taxi pulling up the driveway ♪

04:26.808 --> 04:29.686
♪ I'm coming home soon ♪

04:32.939 --> 04:36.234
♪ I'm coming home soon ♪

04:36.317 --> 04:38.903
♪ Da-da, da-da-da ♪

04:38.987 --> 04:42.073
♪ Da-da-da-da ♪

04:42.156 --> 04:45.285
♪ Da-da, da-da-da ♪

04:45.368 --> 04:47.787
♪ Da-da-da ♪

04:47.870 --> 04:50.957
♪ Da-da, da-da-da ♪♪

04:52.959 --> 04:54.961
[♪♪♪]

04:56.000 --> 05:02.074
