contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

05:04.137 --> 05:08.474
-Casual Tuesday?
-No, I'm actually not going to work today.

05:08.558 --> 05:13.479
I'm going to take Carrie and Caitlyn to school
and then I'm gonna volunteer.

05:13.563 --> 05:15.648
You see what's happening with the Porter Fund?

05:15.732 --> 05:17.942
Good thing your company passed on it.

05:18.026 --> 05:21.321
Yeah, they're Hunter Drew &amp; Associates'
problem now.

05:21.404 --> 05:24.240
When I did take the occasional day off from work,

05:24.324 --> 05:27.952
I always treated myself
to a chocolate éclair at Ross' Bakery.

05:28.036 --> 05:31.247
-I used to love those.
-You can only eat so many muffins in life.

05:32.415 --> 05:34.167
I won't tell Gran you said that.

05:34.834 --> 05:37.420
-Hey, where is she, by the way?
-She had to leave early.

05:37.503 --> 05:39.589
Had some errands to do. Said it was a secret.

05:39.672 --> 05:42.633
-More like harassing Mayor Frank?
-That's my guess.

05:44.677 --> 05:47.221
Uh, hey, are you doing okay?

05:47.305 --> 05:50.224
You've been a little bit on edge
since Gran got back from Ireland.

05:50.308 --> 05:51.726
Have I?

05:51.809 --> 05:55.146
Well, maybe because she didn't tell me
that she was sick.

05:55.229 --> 05:57.231
I could've flown over to help.

05:57.315 --> 06:00.109
-That's probably why she didn't tell you.
-Probably.

06:00.193 --> 06:01.027
[ABBY CHUCKLES]

06:01.110 --> 06:04.238
So a simple day of volunteering without work?

06:04.322 --> 06:05.364
Or talking about work.

06:05.448 --> 06:07.575
I don't think either of us are equipped to do that.

06:07.658 --> 06:10.203
This where you say
the apple doesn't fall far from the tree?

06:10.286 --> 06:13.915
No, this is where I tell you
that I'm very, very proud of you.

06:15.708 --> 06:16.918
Thanks, Dad.

06:17.001 --> 06:18.628
Hey, you guys look excited.

06:18.711 --> 06:20.880
Mom's gonna volunteer for the lunch duties.

06:20.963 --> 06:23.424
-And then help out in my class.
-Yes, math.

06:23.508 --> 06:25.510
I need to brush up on my multiplication tables.

06:27.220 --> 06:29.013
-Good morning!
-Mom, didn't you get my message?

06:29.097 --> 06:32.058
-I'm taking the girls to school today.
-I came to see your father.

06:32.141 --> 06:33.101
Uh-oh.

06:33.184 --> 06:36.437
You know what?
I think I'm going to take your suggestion

06:36.521 --> 06:40.066
and get myself an éclair after I drop the girls off.

06:40.149 --> 06:42.401
You see? The apple doesn't fall far from the tree.

06:42.485 --> 06:44.904
-Now you're channeling me.
-Oh, Dad.

06:44.987 --> 06:48.366
I've been happily channeling you
my whole life. Bye.

06:48.449 --> 06:51.035
-Bye, girls. Have a good day.
GIRLS: Bye.

06:51.119 --> 06:53.246
So, what's your schedule look like?

06:53.329 --> 06:56.624
Well, after this, I'm gonna meet
with some attorneys,

06:56.707 --> 06:59.710
and then lunch, and then I'll meet
with some more attorneys.

06:59.794 --> 07:03.381
And then, just to shake things up,
I'm gonna meet with some attorneys.

07:03.464 --> 07:06.717
If you can pull yourself away
from all that excitement,

07:06.801 --> 07:09.053
I'm gonna go check out venues
for Kevin's wedding.

07:09.137 --> 07:10.596
I'd love your input.

07:10.680 --> 07:12.056
No attorneys, promise.

07:12.140 --> 07:13.599
[♪♪♪]

07:13.683 --> 07:16.352
Darius, I'm telling you, you're gonna love it.

07:17.395 --> 07:21.607
It's a smaller venue, but the sound is first-class.

07:23.109 --> 07:24.902
Three weeks?

07:24.986 --> 07:27.280
No, no, no, that'd be great.

07:28.698 --> 07:31.409
Yeah, I'll come down and visit the family soon.

07:32.452 --> 07:33.286
All right.

07:35.913 --> 07:38.958
For a guy who got his dream back,
you don't seem very happy.

07:39.041 --> 07:42.211
Well, I got the dream,
but no music to accompany it.

07:42.295 --> 07:44.672
I can't find anyone good on short notice.

07:46.090 --> 07:48.885
I'd go with Dierks or Hunter.

07:50.595 --> 07:51.637
Right.

07:54.182 --> 07:55.099
What about you?

07:56.267 --> 07:58.895
-You can't be serious.
-No, I'm serious.

07:58.978 --> 08:02.565
And you'll never find a safer place
to get your feet wet as a performer.

08:02.648 --> 08:03.858
And I'm in a pinch.

08:04.358 --> 08:06.527
I can't do it. I just can't.

08:06.611 --> 08:08.988
Well, just take the day to think about it.

08:10.698 --> 08:11.657
All right?

08:18.539 --> 08:21.209
KEVIN: So you're assuming
I'm picking you as my best man?

08:21.292 --> 08:22.585
I'm your only man.

08:22.668 --> 08:26.380
Connor, we just got engaged,
so maybe just cool it for a bit.

08:26.464 --> 08:29.717
I was cooling it for a bit,
until I hung out with the sisters.

08:29.800 --> 08:34.179
And then I overloaded on happy and joyful,
and now I just can't shake it.

08:35.181 --> 08:37.475
We are just starting to talk about our lives together.

08:37.558 --> 08:40.269
-We have a lot to figure out.
-Our family needs to celebrate.

08:40.352 --> 08:41.812
Our family celebrates everything.

08:41.895 --> 08:45.650
Chesapeake Shores celebrates everything.

08:45.733 --> 08:48.819
I'm just not gonna allow
my wedding to compensate for any of it.

08:48.903 --> 08:49.987
Well, it already has.

08:50.071 --> 08:54.700
I used your wedding as an excuse
for Danielle and I to talk about our future.

08:54.784 --> 08:57.245
-That's very self-serving.
-Yes. Yes, it was.

08:57.328 --> 08:59.872
But it's surprising how much
you can talk about your own life

08:59.956 --> 09:02.375
when you're pretending
to talk about somebody else's.

09:02.458 --> 09:04.210
What have you learned?

09:04.293 --> 09:07.713
Well, I learned that Danielle has
some very strong opinions

09:07.797 --> 09:09.507
about not needing family.

09:10.508 --> 09:12.635
-That's pretty harsh.
-Yeah, I know.

09:14.595 --> 09:16.973
[♪♪♪]

09:20.685 --> 09:22.019
Hi, Gran.

09:22.103 --> 09:23.104
Why are you in a bakery?

09:23.187 --> 09:27.358
-Oh, caught red-handed.
-Wow, I like your kicks.

09:27.441 --> 09:31.028
Yes, well, I'm training for a marathon.

09:31.112 --> 09:33.573
Well, you just had pneumonia, so you be careful.

09:33.656 --> 09:34.490
Thank you.

09:34.574 --> 09:37.827
What is going on here? Have you been
buying your muffins all these years?

09:37.910 --> 09:39.787
Don't be silly.

09:39.870 --> 09:43.082
I had to run business errands early this morning,

09:43.165 --> 09:45.876
and I'm politicking over at city hall.

09:45.960 --> 09:48.379
You mean, harassing Mayor Frank.

09:48.462 --> 09:54.218
You must always remember, it's important
to stay in touch with our elected officials.

09:54.302 --> 09:55.261
You have a lovely day.

09:55.344 --> 09:57.221
-Don't get too many sweets.
-All right.

09:57.305 --> 09:58.764
-Okay.
-Bye, Gran.

10:03.144 --> 10:04.562
Um, excuse me.

10:06.731 --> 10:08.566
Excuse me, sir?

10:09.317 --> 10:10.610
[MUMBLING INDISTINCTLY]

10:12.194 --> 10:14.780
Is that the last éclair?

10:14.864 --> 10:17.366
Mm. You can have it, if you like.

10:18.826 --> 10:19.785
You're joking, right?

10:19.869 --> 10:22.038
If you're hung up, I'll give you the non-bitten end.

10:22.121 --> 10:25.249
-I think I'll pass, thank you.
-Okay, well, suit yourself.

10:25.333 --> 10:26.792
Can you get the door for me?

10:29.128 --> 10:30.296
Are you serious?

10:30.963 --> 10:31.797
Mm.

10:31.881 --> 10:33.507
[♪♪♪]

10:36.969 --> 10:37.803
Thank you.

10:46.604 --> 10:47.980
Are you gonna break up with him?

10:49.148 --> 10:51.692
No. Why would I do that?

10:51.776 --> 10:54.487
Because you're not happy?

10:54.570 --> 10:57.865
So? Lots of people are unhappy in relationships.

10:57.948 --> 11:00.910
That is not a reason that people break up.

11:00.993 --> 11:04.705
Um, I think that's exactly why people break up.

11:04.789 --> 11:09.794
But he's smart and handsome and, um...

11:09.877 --> 11:11.754
sweet and funny.

11:11.837 --> 11:14.340
-And he has an amazing accent.
-All true.

11:14.423 --> 11:17.968
And he cares for me, you know? So, like, maybe...

11:18.052 --> 11:20.304
I mean, you don't necessarily need
to be passionate

11:20.388 --> 11:21.972
to have a passionate connection.

11:22.056 --> 11:25.142
Even for me, that makes no sense.

11:26.644 --> 11:27.686
But he's...

11:29.021 --> 11:29.939
smart, and...

11:31.107 --> 11:33.776
handsome, and sweet, and funny,
and he has an amazing--

11:33.859 --> 11:35.152
Accent?

11:35.236 --> 11:37.571
Yeah, you said that.

11:38.072 --> 11:42.451
So maybe the problem isn't with Simon.

11:42.535 --> 11:46.872
If Simon is, in fact, still Simon,
then maybe the problem is with me.

11:46.956 --> 11:49.375
-What?
-Yeah, maybe I'm the one who changed.

11:49.458 --> 11:54.630
And maybe the problem, therefore,
in the relationship is me.

11:54.713 --> 11:55.548
[BELL JINGLES]

11:55.631 --> 11:56.841
Hold that thought.

11:56.924 --> 11:59.552
Um, so did they accept our offer?

11:59.635 --> 12:02.430
It turns out we never had a chance.

12:02.513 --> 12:04.932
The other buyer is this guy Andy Medina.

12:06.559 --> 12:08.519
-Do you know him?
-No, but I did some research.

12:08.602 --> 12:11.605
They're this D.C.-based couple
that's trying to spread their holdings

12:11.689 --> 12:13.858
across the Eastern Seaboard.

12:13.941 --> 12:16.777
Very wealthy. The only chance
that we're gonna outbid them

12:16.861 --> 12:20.906
is if we, uh, call my mom and dad.

12:20.990 --> 12:24.034
-I just shivered a little.
-Me too.

12:24.118 --> 12:29.165
Okay. So we just need to convince
the seller to take less money.

12:29.248 --> 12:31.667
Simple. People love less money.

12:31.750 --> 12:35.754
-How are you gonna do that?
-I don't know. But I'm excited.

12:38.507 --> 12:40.259
KEVIN: Hey, Abby.
-Hey.

12:40.342 --> 12:42.094
-Need your opinion.
-What about?

12:42.178 --> 12:45.097
Yeah. I'm wondering how soon would be too soon

12:45.181 --> 12:47.683
to ask Uncle Thomas to go back
to my normal caseload.

12:47.766 --> 12:50.060
Connor, I would have fired you for what you did.

12:50.144 --> 12:52.521
You should be working for Dad,
he said the same thing.

12:52.605 --> 12:54.690
-Abby O'Brien Winters?
-Yes?

12:54.773 --> 12:56.066
You've been served.

12:57.276 --> 12:59.570
[♪♪♪]

13:00.362 --> 13:02.615
What's going on? Is it the Porter Fund?

13:04.575 --> 13:05.993
ABBY:
I'm late, I gotta go.

13:10.498 --> 13:12.458
[♪♪♪]

13:15.002 --> 13:19.590
So if Caroline is back
with her ex-boyfriend in Carolina,

13:19.673 --> 13:21.717
what's happening with Caroline and Carl?

13:22.259 --> 13:23.511
I have no idea.

13:23.594 --> 13:28.265
But I will keep my alliterations
to myself next time around.

13:28.349 --> 13:33.020
In my manuscript, I accidentally had
Carl passionately kissing a Southern state.

13:33.103 --> 13:35.189
-You know, Caroline, Carolina?
-Mmm.

13:37.233 --> 13:41.028
You know, passion is very important

13:41.111 --> 13:44.365
in any relationship.

13:44.448 --> 13:45.908
True, true.

13:45.991 --> 13:48.827
Passion sells books,
but, you know, passion does fade.

13:49.495 --> 13:53.624
You know, I would take respect,
shared values, sense of humor...

13:53.707 --> 13:55.084
Ah.

13:55.167 --> 13:56.502
Perhaps fresh fruit.

13:56.585 --> 13:59.672
Oh, but one bite can get you
into so much trouble, though.

13:59.755 --> 14:01.131
Only if you're tempted.

14:02.216 --> 14:06.428
-I'm sorry to interrupt! It's an emergency.
-No, it is not an emergency.

14:06.512 --> 14:07.888
Yes, it is.

14:07.972 --> 14:09.807
-Tempted?
-Terrified.

14:11.267 --> 14:13.310
KEVIN:
So we need to pick between three photographers,

14:13.394 --> 14:16.355
two videographers
and some crazy florist that Gran found.

14:18.440 --> 14:20.276
Are you having second thoughts?

14:21.694 --> 14:24.530
Because if you are, I have two brothers
that would love nothing more

14:24.613 --> 14:25.948
than to play you in football.

14:26.031 --> 14:29.618
No, I prefer having my head attached to my spine.

14:29.702 --> 14:32.204
It's just, when I thought about getting married,

14:32.288 --> 14:35.124
I guess I never really gave
too much thought to the actual wedding.

14:35.207 --> 14:39.920
Yeah, me neither. Never been much
of a lace-and-ribbon kind of girl.

14:40.004 --> 14:44.216
Then you're gonna hate
the fire-resistant pink overalls that I got you.

14:44.758 --> 14:46.302
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

14:49.179 --> 14:51.849
Never thought I'd be walking down the aisle again.

14:51.932 --> 14:53.601
Are you having second thoughts?

14:53.684 --> 14:55.436
I'm just saying that since we got engaged,

14:55.519 --> 14:58.063
it's been a blur.

14:58.147 --> 14:59.273
But a great one.

14:59.356 --> 15:01.275
Yeah, for me too.

15:02.818 --> 15:04.820
[♪♪♪]

15:14.204 --> 15:16.415
JAY:
If you followed me to get the last éclair, it's gone.

15:18.417 --> 15:19.877
Uh...

15:19.960 --> 15:22.755
I'm here for my two daughters.
What are you doing here?

15:22.838 --> 15:24.840
Uh, my 30 kids.

15:24.924 --> 15:27.635
Boys, girls, all different moms.

15:27.718 --> 15:30.971
Jay Ross, third grade teacher
slash playground monitor.

15:33.474 --> 15:36.977
-No, you were behind the counter.
-Slash Ruth Ross' nephew.

15:37.061 --> 15:40.147
It's not exactly stealing if it's your aunt's bakery.

15:41.231 --> 15:43.275
Just moved here from Greenville, South Carolina.

15:43.359 --> 15:46.278
Uh... Well... Sorry.

15:47.571 --> 15:50.866
-It's your first time volunteering?
-Uh, yeah, how'd you know?

15:50.950 --> 15:52.826
Well, they give cleanup duty to the newbies,

15:52.910 --> 15:55.079
mostly to keep them
out of the way of everyone else.

15:55.162 --> 15:59.041
But if you do a good job,
they might bump you up to classroom helper.

15:59.124 --> 16:02.711
Well, I don't think I'm going to be here
long enough to get promoted, so...

16:02.795 --> 16:05.422
Let me guess, the high school's poaching you.

16:05.506 --> 16:09.009
No, I'm, um, actually, uh...

16:09.885 --> 16:13.806
I was the vice president
of a consulting firm in Baltimore,

16:13.889 --> 16:17.685
-so, uh, I'm just taking a leave.
-Mm.

16:17.768 --> 16:20.771
Well, for a high-powered executive,
you are doing remarkably well.

16:20.854 --> 16:26.694
It's just that the plastic goes in the yellow
and the composting goes in the green.

16:28.445 --> 16:29.446
There we go.

16:29.530 --> 16:31.824
Hey, look, I can help you if you need a hand--

16:31.907 --> 16:34.243
No, I got it, I got it, I got it. I'm good.

16:34.326 --> 16:36.328
[♪♪♪]

16:43.877 --> 16:46.964
You know, if you make a mistake,
I'm not gonna turn you in.

16:49.258 --> 16:53.846
No, it's not that.
I just am dealing with a lot right now.

17:01.812 --> 17:02.980
[JAY CLEARS THROAT]

17:05.941 --> 17:07.734
-Juice box?
-It's berry blast.

17:07.818 --> 17:10.779
Usually keep an extra one on me
for just this sort of thing.

17:11.446 --> 17:12.906
Oh, sorry, I...

17:14.366 --> 17:15.200
Abby.

17:15.284 --> 17:16.242
I'm, uh...

17:18.037 --> 17:19.371
Carrie and Caitlyn's mom.

17:19.454 --> 17:22.708
Oh, the Winters girls. Well, you have great kids.

17:24.126 --> 17:27.880
You know, that almost makes me sorry
for taking the last éclair.

17:27.963 --> 17:29.673
-Almost?
-Yeah.

17:29.757 --> 17:32.051
It was really, really good.

17:34.261 --> 17:35.262
[JAY CHUCKLES]

17:35.971 --> 17:37.973
[COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

17:40.517 --> 17:42.936
I thought there was supposed
to be live music today.

17:44.313 --> 17:46.398
I'm working on it. You guys good?

17:46.482 --> 17:47.608
JESS:
Mm-hm.

17:47.691 --> 17:51.111
Okay, so it looks like Hal Keown likes
to take his family

17:51.195 --> 17:52.780
for Friday night dinner at Chez Maison.

17:52.863 --> 17:54.490
SIMON:
It looks like he loves his children.

17:54.573 --> 17:56.992
Yeah, every picture is with him and his kids.

17:57.076 --> 17:59.536
Okay, so my plan is, we grab him,

17:59.620 --> 18:02.414
hold him down
and force him to sell us the property.

18:02.498 --> 18:04.500
Yeah, that sounds an awful lot like kidnapping.

18:04.583 --> 18:06.335
Not to mention extortion.

18:06.418 --> 18:09.421
-That's one way to look at it.
-It's the only way to look at it.

18:09.505 --> 18:12.132
Okay, so then we just force him
to sell us the property.

18:12.216 --> 18:15.302
Or we show up to the restaurant and just ask.

18:15.385 --> 18:17.387
Better. I like your thinking.

18:17.471 --> 18:19.223
-Whenever you're ready.
SIMON: Thank you.

18:19.306 --> 18:22.184
DANIELLE: You don't know them like I do.
CONNOR: They can't be that bad.

18:24.728 --> 18:27.481
EMMA: Let me know if you need anything else.
-Yes, thank you.

18:27.564 --> 18:29.983
You just gotta think of it this way:

18:30.067 --> 18:31.360
The glass is half full.

18:31.443 --> 18:35.155
Sorry, but with my family,
the glass is more half empty.

18:36.990 --> 18:37.825
Danielle.

18:38.909 --> 18:42.162
-At some point, you gotta forgive.
-Or not.

18:45.207 --> 18:47.126
JESS:
We're going on a secret mission. Are you in?

18:47.209 --> 18:49.044
It's not secret. It's just dinner.

18:49.128 --> 18:52.005
-If you're making dinner, then we're in.
-Even better, I'm paying.

18:52.089 --> 18:53.465
-We're in.
CONNOR: Yeah, we're in.

18:53.549 --> 18:54.591
JESS:
Okay.

18:54.675 --> 18:56.009
-We'll catch up with you, okay?
-Okay.

18:56.093 --> 18:58.637
SIMON: So, what's the plan again?
BREE: We agreed on kidnapping...

18:58.720 --> 19:02.182
Hey. Stage is all yours if you want it.

19:02.266 --> 19:05.018
-I can't. I'm not ready.
-You're never gonna feel ready.

19:05.102 --> 19:06.937
You just gotta dive in.

19:07.020 --> 19:10.399
-And drown?
-Come on. I'm not gonna let you drown.

19:13.152 --> 19:13.986
What are you doing?

19:14.069 --> 19:16.613
Rule number one,
never go on stage unannounced.

19:20.826 --> 19:23.829
Hey, I got a treat for y'all today.

19:23.912 --> 19:26.582
A new emerging country artist.

19:26.665 --> 19:29.501
This is her first gig, so she's a little nervous,

19:29.585 --> 19:33.422
but I think she's got talent,
and I know you're gonna think so too.

19:33.505 --> 19:35.757
So give it up for Emma Rogers!

19:46.268 --> 19:47.269
[EMMA CLEARS THROAT]

19:50.022 --> 19:51.732
So this is called "Sometime."

19:55.277 --> 19:57.654
♪ Never been the kind ♪

19:57.738 --> 20:01.617
♪ To wear a one-size-fits-all dream ♪

20:05.037 --> 20:09.458
♪ I like the sound
Of singing my own song ♪♪

20:12.711 --> 20:14.087
Take it from the intro?

20:29.311 --> 20:31.772
♪ Never been the kind ♪

20:31.855 --> 20:36.443
♪ To wear a one-size-fits-all dream ♪

20:36.526 --> 20:41.365
♪ I like the sound
Of singing my own song ♪

20:43.992 --> 20:46.870
♪ Followed every broken road ♪

20:46.954 --> 20:51.208
♪ But it never felt right to me ♪

20:51.291 --> 20:56.213
♪ I couldn't find a place
Where I belong ♪

20:57.381 --> 20:59.591
♪ Sometimes ♪

20:59.675 --> 21:05.264
♪ When the night is dark
And the world wants to take my heart ♪

21:05.347 --> 21:10.227
♪ And it feels like the sun
Will never shine ♪♪

21:10.310 --> 21:12.187
MICK:
All right, I'll see you back at the office.

21:12.271 --> 21:15.774
And let Dilpher know
I'm not making deals, all right?

21:15.857 --> 21:17.067
Okay, thanks.

21:18.068 --> 21:19.319
So much for closing your eyes

21:19.403 --> 21:21.238
and pretending everything's gonna be okay.

21:21.321 --> 21:25.075
Well, it's hard to close your eyes
when people are taking swings at you.

21:25.158 --> 21:28.370
They're shutting down
my biggest development project in Chicago.

21:28.453 --> 21:30.080
Oh, no, Mick.

21:30.706 --> 21:34.001
I'm sorry, it's probably not the best time
to be looking at wedding sites.

21:34.084 --> 21:36.628
No, it's fine. It's keeping my mind off the bad stuff.

21:36.712 --> 21:37.921
Yeah, me too.

21:38.005 --> 21:41.174
I am still trying to figure out what I wanna do next.

21:41.258 --> 21:43.719
-Any ideas?
-Not really.

21:45.637 --> 21:47.889
But I miss curating.

21:49.599 --> 21:52.436
Especially helping young artists get their start.

21:55.022 --> 21:57.274
-What? You think that's funny?
-No, no, it's just you.

21:57.357 --> 21:59.401
You're always so busy helping everybody else,

21:59.484 --> 22:01.403
you have no time for yourself.

22:01.486 --> 22:03.989
It's a good thing. It's admirable.

22:04.072 --> 22:06.074
[♪♪♪]

22:07.576 --> 22:10.537
Oh, look. They must've just had a wedding here.

22:16.376 --> 22:19.546
Hasn't changed, has it, since we got married here?

22:19.629 --> 22:20.964
It's a little drier.

22:21.048 --> 22:23.884
I remember trying to walk down the aisle

22:23.967 --> 22:28.263
with my heels digging into the ground, just praying.

22:28.346 --> 22:31.058
"Don't fall, please don't fall."

22:31.141 --> 22:34.853
Thomas kept whispering,
"She's gonna fall, she's gonna fall."

22:34.936 --> 22:36.313
But I didn't, did I?

22:37.397 --> 22:40.025
No, you didn't.

23:05.258 --> 23:07.260
[♪♪♪]

23:09.429 --> 23:12.766
-Kevin? What are you still doing here?
-Don't even ask.

23:12.849 --> 23:15.393
Mom wants us to get married on the Bluff,

23:15.477 --> 23:18.730
but Sarah and I still haven't even picked a date yet.

23:20.190 --> 23:22.567
Oh, the Bluff.

23:22.651 --> 23:25.612
Trace and I talked about getting married here
when we were kids.

23:25.695 --> 23:29.866
I actually still go here sometimes
when I'm trying to figure stuff out.

23:30.575 --> 23:31.660
So how are you doing?

23:32.410 --> 23:36.248
Well, you know, everything is a little bit crazy.

23:36.331 --> 23:39.835
-Well, I'm impressed.
-What, that my life is imploding?

23:39.918 --> 23:43.296
No, that you stuck up
for what you believe in. You're a hero.

23:44.589 --> 23:46.383
-I'm definitely not a hero.
-Yeah, you are.

23:46.466 --> 23:47.467
A hero is just

23:47.551 --> 23:50.554
someone who makes a decision
that no one else has the courage to make.

23:57.602 --> 24:00.272
So the Bluff?

24:00.355 --> 24:02.983
Yeah, Mom says it's
the "place where dreams come true."

24:03.066 --> 24:05.277
I do remember that from the brochure.

24:08.655 --> 24:11.324
[COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

24:14.828 --> 24:17.998
-Now it's your turn?
-To convince you to go back on the road?

24:18.081 --> 24:22.002
Nah. You know as well as I do,
no one can convince you of anything.

24:22.085 --> 24:23.837
But you're not gonna stop trying, are you?

24:23.920 --> 24:26.965
I wouldn't be much of a manager if I didn't try.

24:28.008 --> 24:30.260
You always did have a good eye for talent.

24:31.261 --> 24:32.804
You gonna introduce me?

24:32.888 --> 24:36.224
Mark, look, she's talented, but she's not ready.

24:36.308 --> 24:39.895
Well, don't you think
you ought to leave that up to her?

24:44.941 --> 24:45.775
Hey, Emma.

24:50.572 --> 24:53.241
Emma Rogers, this is Mark Hall.

24:53.325 --> 24:55.285
-He was my manager--
-I know who he is.

24:55.368 --> 24:57.746
-Pleasure to meet you, Mr. Hall.
-I'm Mark to my friends.

24:57.829 --> 25:00.040
I saw you on-stage.

25:00.123 --> 25:04.336
Not sure about your lead guitar,
but you're the real deal.

25:04.419 --> 25:07.088
-Well, if that's it, I'm gonna get back.
-Uh, not quite.

25:07.172 --> 25:10.592
Not yet. I think I'll stick around for a drink.

25:11.343 --> 25:13.845
Make yourself at home. First round's on me.

25:14.679 --> 25:15.764
Just the first?

25:15.847 --> 25:18.767
-Gotta keep the lights on.
-I'll get you that drink.

25:18.850 --> 25:20.393
Much obliged.

25:21.728 --> 25:25.815
So I'm thinking the Bluff will work out perfectly
for Kevin and Sarah.

25:25.899 --> 25:28.526
Oh, yeah, that's great. That's a beautiful spot.

25:28.610 --> 25:32.739
And for music, I always prefer a band over a DJ.

25:32.822 --> 25:36.243
It's more expensive, but the music makes the night.

25:36.326 --> 25:38.453
Then a band it is. Perfect for the first dance.

25:38.536 --> 25:43.124
Yeah. And a harpist for the ceremony
and the first kiss.

25:45.252 --> 25:46.628
Uh...

25:46.711 --> 25:50.423
So, Mick, back there at the gazebo, um...

25:51.549 --> 25:54.469
I'm thinking there's a million reasons
why that was a bad idea.

25:54.552 --> 25:57.097
-And very few why it was a good one.
-Yes.

25:57.180 --> 25:59.307
We've been down that road,
we know where it leads.

25:59.391 --> 26:02.852
-Invariably will lead us there again.
-Exactly, so...

26:02.936 --> 26:05.272
-I don't think we should-- Okay.
-Yeah. Yeah.

26:05.355 --> 26:07.983
[♪♪♪]

26:12.654 --> 26:14.239
There he is. Come on.

26:14.322 --> 26:17.284
Hey. Hey, we-- We can't just seat ourselves.

26:21.621 --> 26:23.873
Peck? Party of six? Right this way.

26:25.583 --> 26:28.169
CONNOR: Do we have a plan?
-Who needs plans?

26:28.253 --> 26:30.130
Um, everybody?

26:32.841 --> 26:35.677
-Do you wanna talk to him? Or me?
-I could, I'm an attorney.

26:35.760 --> 26:37.762
-I'm an attorney too.
CONNOR: True.

26:37.846 --> 26:38.722
JESS:
Um...

26:39.639 --> 26:41.182
It's so nice to be spending

26:41.266 --> 26:43.601
our five-year anniversary here, David Peck.

26:47.355 --> 26:49.232
Have they been here before?

26:49.316 --> 26:52.986
This is, after all, where we got engaged, David.

26:53.069 --> 26:56.406
And I know how much family means to you.

26:56.489 --> 26:57.824
-Mm-hm.
-Of course.

26:57.907 --> 27:00.160
This is also where I told you I was pregnant.

27:00.243 --> 27:02.495
-With our twins.
DANIELLE: Little Shannon.

27:02.579 --> 27:04.748
Yeah, and Kayje.

27:04.831 --> 27:06.124
Kayje?

27:06.207 --> 27:09.085
And I cried when-- His?

27:09.169 --> 27:11.296
He hit his first home run.

27:11.379 --> 27:14.799
And I cried at Shannon's first recital.

27:14.883 --> 27:16.551
And when Kayje graduated high school.

27:18.678 --> 27:21.890
That's when I'm gonna be crying so, so much.

27:21.973 --> 27:26.728
It's just too bad that Hal Keown won't sell us
the bed-and-breakfast.

27:27.979 --> 27:28.855
CONNOR:
Shame.

27:29.731 --> 27:31.358
Shame.

27:31.441 --> 27:33.360
I appreciate the effort, Jess.

27:33.443 --> 27:37.280
But Andy Medina and his wife tried
to do the same thing last week.

27:42.535 --> 27:45.997
Well, that didn't work out as planned.

27:46.081 --> 27:47.123
So...?

27:48.333 --> 27:51.795
Jess O'Brien, may I have this dance?

27:52.796 --> 27:54.798
Yes, you may, David Peck.

28:00.178 --> 28:03.556
It's okay. We're gonna be okay.

28:03.640 --> 28:05.975
-Okay.
-We're always...

28:07.519 --> 28:09.938
-gonna be okay.
-Okay.

28:11.147 --> 28:12.148
Kayje?

28:12.232 --> 28:14.317
That was Connor.

28:14.401 --> 28:16.403
Okay. Well, next time, let's name them together.

28:16.486 --> 28:17.320
Okay.

28:19.531 --> 28:20.907
Do you wanna dance?

28:22.242 --> 28:23.410
[SIMON SCOFFS]

28:23.493 --> 28:28.289
With no music? I don't know.
It's a bit of a rom-com cliché, isn't it?

28:28.373 --> 28:30.708
-I actually put that in Eternal Caroline.
BREE: Yeah.

28:31.709 --> 28:35.505
Maybe I could put it in my next one,
Step in Time, Caroline.

28:35.588 --> 28:37.465
Or how about Carry On, Caroline?

28:39.050 --> 28:41.886
-Excuse me.
-Uh, Bree?

28:43.638 --> 28:46.307
I'm sorry. Excuse me. Bree.

28:49.310 --> 28:51.062
[♪♪♪]

28:51.604 --> 28:53.732
Bree? Bree.

28:54.733 --> 28:55.859
You okay?

28:57.152 --> 28:58.153
Um...

28:59.654 --> 29:01.573
No, I'm not. I, um...

29:04.325 --> 29:07.537
I feel like we're not connecting,
and I don't know why.

29:09.122 --> 29:14.085
Uh, yeah. Yeah, I know. I feel it too.

29:14.169 --> 29:17.005
I think we're both trying too hard.

29:17.547 --> 29:22.218
-We're not picking up where we left off.
-Like we used to.

29:22.302 --> 29:23.553
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

29:25.889 --> 29:29.893
Maybe we just need to get out
of our heads a little bit.

29:30.852 --> 29:34.522
Like do and not think?

29:35.106 --> 29:35.940
Mm.

29:54.042 --> 29:56.252
[♪♪♪]

29:58.421 --> 30:01.132
What is going on between you and Mick?

30:02.467 --> 30:04.719
Nothing. We just decided to be friends.

30:05.762 --> 30:09.766
Oh, come on. Nell, at this point in our life,
it's better for everyone, including us.

30:09.849 --> 30:12.977
It is smart, it is safe and it is sensible.

30:13.061 --> 30:14.604
And maybe it's silly.

30:15.647 --> 30:19.609
Megan, I have had a blessed life.

30:19.692 --> 30:23.947
Oh-ho. Charmed in almost every way, for sure.

30:24.030 --> 30:27.575
But I've gathered up my fair share of mistakes.

30:27.659 --> 30:30.954
And I can tell you this, if I had not,

30:31.037 --> 30:34.833
I would not be here now, with you. Oh, no.

30:34.916 --> 30:40.171
And I would not have my wonderful sons
and my beautiful grandchildren.

30:40.713 --> 30:42.757
We hurt a lot of people, Nell.

30:44.175 --> 30:45.552
I know we hurt each other.

30:45.635 --> 30:49.305
-How do you know that'd happen again?
-Because it could.

30:50.431 --> 30:51.558
Ah.

30:52.058 --> 30:55.895
And if it does, you'll heal yourself.

30:57.814 --> 31:02.026
It's a lot easier to live with mistakes than regrets.

31:04.737 --> 31:07.365
BREE:
Well, maybe you can find another inn.

31:08.741 --> 31:12.328
I don't know if you know how hard it is
to find the perfect B and B.

31:12.412 --> 31:13.997
Wasn't your last place perfect?

31:14.622 --> 31:18.334
I don't know if you know how hard it is
to find two perfect B and B's.

31:19.544 --> 31:21.963
Or one perfect guy.

31:25.425 --> 31:27.427
I think my head's done talking.

31:28.678 --> 31:31.139
Does that mean you're ready
to listen to your heart?

31:31.222 --> 31:32.432
[BREE SIGHS]

31:35.768 --> 31:37.186
Simon isn't the one.

31:40.690 --> 31:43.860
I just really, really, really wish he was.

31:46.613 --> 31:48.907
Ahem. How are things with Danielle?

31:51.451 --> 31:52.368
I don't know.

31:54.454 --> 31:59.250
Sometimes it feels like
we're not as compatible as we used to be.

32:00.043 --> 32:01.502
Well, what happened?

32:03.129 --> 32:07.300
Well, lately, it just seems like
we're on different pages.

32:07.383 --> 32:10.511
But I'm not gonna give up.

32:10.595 --> 32:12.805
-We've been through too much.
BREE: Hm.

32:12.889 --> 32:16.809
And I'm not gonna give up on my new inn.

32:19.437 --> 32:21.439
[♪♪♪]

32:22.482 --> 32:24.025
Oh, here she comes.

32:24.943 --> 32:26.361
You don't have a plan, do you?

32:26.444 --> 32:29.656
Oh, yeah. I got a plan. A really horrible plan.

32:29.739 --> 32:33.618
And it involves very, very high heels.

32:33.701 --> 32:36.245
Connor, I know how to make you feel better.

32:36.329 --> 32:37.622
We're going shopping.

32:44.212 --> 32:46.214
[COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

32:51.094 --> 32:52.512
Hey, how are you?

32:56.182 --> 32:57.684
-Mick.
-Hey.

32:59.102 --> 33:02.146
-How's it feel to be home?
-Like I never left.

33:02.230 --> 33:04.065
This place has always been about the music.

33:04.148 --> 33:08.236
But I gotta give Chris credit,
the books are meticulous.

33:08.319 --> 33:10.113
-At least he was good for something.
-Yeah.

33:10.780 --> 33:14.826
You know, I wanted to thank you
for trusting in me, Mick.

33:14.909 --> 33:17.996
-I won't let you down again.
-That's good to hear.

33:18.079 --> 33:20.039
At least I'll have one partner who's on the level.

33:20.748 --> 33:25.420
-Yeah, I kind of heard. How you doing?
-I'll get through it.

33:26.879 --> 33:29.465
-And Abby?
-She'll find her way.

33:30.717 --> 33:33.052
Yeah. Yeah, she will.

33:35.638 --> 33:36.931
All right. See you, Mick.

33:47.358 --> 33:49.402
[♪♪♪]

33:52.113 --> 33:54.115
[WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

33:54.991 --> 33:56.409
WOMAN:
It has to be done.

33:57.577 --> 34:01.164
Without a doubt,
it will triple our money on that easily.

34:01.831 --> 34:03.750
JESS:
Good afternoon, Mr. and Mrs. Medina.

34:03.833 --> 34:07.879
-Yes?
-Hi. I am Shannon Kayje.

34:07.962 --> 34:11.716
I represent the Pecks.
The Boston Pecks, from Boston.

34:13.092 --> 34:16.679
And why would
the Boston Pecks wanna talk to us?

34:16.763 --> 34:20.725
Mr. Medina, Mr. and Mrs. Peck have noticed
that you're expanding

34:20.808 --> 34:23.478
your property portfolio up and down the coast,

34:23.561 --> 34:25.980
and I am here as a courtesy to let you know

34:26.063 --> 34:29.609
that they too are interested in the little inn
in Chesapeake Shores.

34:29.692 --> 34:31.652
I wasn't aware the Pecks were involved.

34:32.527 --> 34:33.612
They are.

34:33.696 --> 34:37.241
And I would be remiss
if I didn't remind you of the ramifications

34:37.324 --> 34:38.951
of an unsightly bidding war.

34:39.034 --> 34:41.996
Is it true? Stockholm in '96?

34:42.080 --> 34:45.458
I am neither at liberty to confirm or deny.

34:46.667 --> 34:48.878
How do I know you are who you say you are?

34:48.960 --> 34:50.838
It does seem rather convenient.

34:50.922 --> 34:53.757
Maybe I can help clear things up.
David Peck. Sorry I'm late.

34:53.841 --> 34:57.512
-I see you've met my--
-Me, Shannon Kayje, his assistant.

34:58.137 --> 34:58.971
DAVID:
Ahem.

34:59.055 --> 35:02.350
I've let them know that your parents would like
to avoid a bidding war.

35:02.433 --> 35:06.312
Ah, yes. Those are so unsightly.

35:07.230 --> 35:09.982
The Pecks would love to be here,
but they're currently unpacking

35:10.066 --> 35:11.984
from a soiree in Gstaad.

35:13.402 --> 35:15.113
The one with the G.

35:15.196 --> 35:17.490
Gstaad, so...

35:20.952 --> 35:23.162
So there's a black-and-white photographer

35:23.246 --> 35:25.373
your mom wants us to meet in New York.

35:25.456 --> 35:26.499
New York?

35:26.582 --> 35:29.335
And she also thought we could set up
some appointments

35:29.418 --> 35:31.170
at some bridal shops in D.C.

35:32.338 --> 35:35.383
I don't know if I can handle a whole year of this.

35:35.466 --> 35:38.719
-I guess if it's what everyone wants.
-Yeah. But what do you want?

35:41.222 --> 35:42.473
I just want you.

35:43.474 --> 35:44.851
I just want you.

35:44.934 --> 35:46.936
[♪♪♪]

35:48.312 --> 35:52.275
You know, we O'Briens have a tendency
of overcomplicating everything.

35:52.358 --> 35:54.360
And my family, not so much.

35:54.443 --> 35:55.278
KEVIN:
Hmm.

35:56.279 --> 35:58.072
Maybe there's a compromise.

35:59.407 --> 36:00.825
I'm good with whatever you want.

36:02.285 --> 36:05.288
-You mean it?
-I do.

36:10.084 --> 36:11.210
Then I do too.

36:15.673 --> 36:18.009
[♪♪♪]

36:21.554 --> 36:22.513
Easy.

36:23.931 --> 36:25.600
Um, hey.

36:25.683 --> 36:29.353
You know, when we talk about the future
and our families,

36:29.437 --> 36:32.356
I'm a little concerned about what you say.

36:33.274 --> 36:34.692
What do you mean?

36:34.775 --> 36:37.195
Well, I know you're not close with your family,

36:37.278 --> 36:40.489
but lately I've been getting a lot closer with mine.

36:40.573 --> 36:43.534
And it hasn't always been great,
but it's getting better.

36:43.618 --> 36:49.123
I know. But that's your family, not mine.

36:49.207 --> 36:53.711
I know, but even when things were really bad,

36:53.794 --> 36:56.130
I always had hope that they would get better.

36:56.214 --> 36:59.800
But you don't seem that bothered by your situation.

36:59.884 --> 37:02.511
Connor, every family is different.

37:02.595 --> 37:07.308
And mine's not like yours.

37:07.391 --> 37:11.437
But that's what I like about you.

37:12.897 --> 37:16.609
In fact, I, um...

37:20.905 --> 37:21.989
I love you.

37:47.181 --> 37:49.600
JESS:
If the inn doesn't work out, we should be spies.

37:49.684 --> 37:53.854
DAVID: I told them who I really am.
-No, you were just playing the part of David Peck.

37:53.938 --> 37:55.731
DAVID:
But I am David Peck.

37:56.399 --> 37:59.193
So my mom called.

37:59.277 --> 38:00.528
Oh.

38:00.611 --> 38:02.280
How is Deidra?

38:02.363 --> 38:03.906
She's good.

38:03.990 --> 38:07.326
But she said that some weird couple,
the Medinas, called,

38:07.410 --> 38:11.205
and they started babbling about not wanting
to repeat Stockholm in '96.

38:12.206 --> 38:14.000
That was unsightly.

38:14.083 --> 38:19.255
Yeah, and she said
that the Medinas started apologizing profusely.

38:19.338 --> 38:23.968
And they wanted to send their regards
to a Shannon Kayje.

38:24.051 --> 38:26.846
They asked me if I knew anything about it.

38:26.929 --> 38:29.223
And what did you say?

38:29.307 --> 38:31.934
Well, I said that Shannon Kayje

38:32.435 --> 38:36.522
was the best thing to happen
to this family in a long time.

38:38.607 --> 38:41.986
Well, you're the best thing
that happened to me in a long time.

38:42.069 --> 38:44.071
[♪♪♪]

38:45.406 --> 38:46.991
It's perfect.

39:00.129 --> 39:01.213
Can't find the words?

39:04.633 --> 39:06.427
No. Not--

39:06.510 --> 39:08.387
Not this time.

39:08.471 --> 39:10.639
Well, I think that I might.

39:11.807 --> 39:15.311
It's an idea that I've had for the ending
of my latest Caroline novel.

39:15.394 --> 39:17.396
Step in Time, Caroline?

39:17.480 --> 39:18.314
Yeah.

39:18.397 --> 39:21.359
I was hoping that I might run it by you.

39:21.859 --> 39:24.362
Actually, Simon, um...

39:24.445 --> 39:26.405
I need to talk to you, and it's--

39:26.489 --> 39:30.868
"He looked out at the water's edge,

39:30.951 --> 39:35.373
seeing her blond hair reflect
the last rays of light from the setting sun."

39:36.499 --> 39:38.584
Very pretty, but--

39:38.667 --> 39:42.296
"But he knew that it was time to leave.

39:43.464 --> 39:47.510
That their love was not destined
to stand the tests of time."

39:48.594 --> 39:50.763
You know me, I love clichés.

39:50.846 --> 39:53.099
Bread and butter of all hack novelists.

39:53.891 --> 39:55.643
[♪♪♪]

39:56.435 --> 39:59.897
"For although he loved her dearly,

40:00.898 --> 40:07.655
their time together was but a sonnet,
a minuet, a precious moment."

40:08.823 --> 40:09.865
Simon.

40:12.493 --> 40:15.079
Bree, I'm reading.

40:17.790 --> 40:19.250
"So he turned away...

40:20.960 --> 40:26.215
knowing that her love had changed him forever...

40:27.258 --> 40:32.096
and hoping that his love had done
the same for her."

40:34.849 --> 40:35.975
Yeah.

40:37.351 --> 40:40.312
I-- I don't know where I'd be if you hadn't--

40:40.396 --> 40:44.650
"He sees through her
to the point where she is invisible."

40:47.403 --> 40:48.279
Oh...

40:49.822 --> 40:53.242
I knew-- I knew that you were unhappy, Bree.

40:55.119 --> 40:58.789
But it would hurt me too much
to know that I'm responsible.

41:11.427 --> 41:13.304
-I'm so sorry.
-No. No.

41:36.494 --> 41:38.496
[♪♪♪]

41:56.430 --> 41:58.098
Oh, thank you.

41:59.183 --> 42:01.227
So I was wondering if I could make the toast.

42:01.310 --> 42:02.895
Oh, sure. Have at it.

42:04.647 --> 42:08.651
I have been in love only one time in my life,

42:08.734 --> 42:10.528
and it did not turn out well.

42:11.195 --> 42:14.156
No offense, Megan,
maybe I should do the toast next time.

42:14.240 --> 42:15.616
-I'm not finished.
-Oh.

42:16.659 --> 42:19.453
But I still care about that person.

42:20.621 --> 42:24.583
And I don't want to walk away
from what could be by fearing what was.

42:28.629 --> 42:33.175
I've hired a local harpist for the wedding
and talked to Sarah about the invitations.

42:35.803 --> 42:39.181
Oh, the O'Briens make everything complicated.

42:42.601 --> 42:43.644
Overly complicated.

42:44.436 --> 42:45.688
[GLASSES CLINK]

42:49.358 --> 42:53.654
TRACE: You should know, with Mark Hall,
take everything with a grain of salt.

42:53.737 --> 42:55.197
I kind of got that vibe.

42:55.281 --> 42:57.992
So, what'd he offer you?

42:58.075 --> 42:59.952
What most people would sell their soul for.

43:01.245 --> 43:02.663
Sounds about right.

43:03.831 --> 43:04.999
And?

43:05.082 --> 43:08.794
And I'm not ready. And I got this familiar feeling.

43:08.877 --> 43:11.714
Same one I got before I ditched
my boyfriend in Atlanta.

43:11.797 --> 43:13.757
You sign up, you lose control.

43:13.841 --> 43:16.135
Like switching out one bad relationship for another.

43:17.720 --> 43:21.265
You know, I don't feel that way with you.

43:29.940 --> 43:31.942
[♪♪♪]

44:00.971 --> 44:02.973
[♪♪♪]

44:30.250 --> 44:32.795
NARRATOR:
Next week on Chesapeake Shores:

44:32.878 --> 44:34.588
So the answer's still no?

44:34.672 --> 44:37.841
The answer has been no
since I walked off stage in Prague.

44:37.925 --> 44:40.427
-I was asking Emma.
ABBY: I have had enough real,

44:40.511 --> 44:42.888
between work and the ship and...

44:42.971 --> 44:44.515
-Trace?
JAY: The sets were destroyed.

44:44.598 --> 44:47.434
The school play is this week,
and two of my students said that you--

44:47.518 --> 44:49.895
Wait a sec. Carrie and Caitlyn Winters?

44:49.978 --> 44:51.814
Mick and I have to say something
to the kids, don't we?

44:51.897 --> 44:54.108
You already know the answer.

44:54.191 --> 44:55.609
We have an announcement to make.

